-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GPLv3 software for a tool that helps in the creation of virtual 
machine networks.

See directory cloonix for the LICENCE

See cloonix.fr for more documentation.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------


Build and install from github sources:
--------------------------------------

  For each distribution, packets have to be installed for the build, see the
  "REQUIRED PACKETS FOR BUILD" chapter for the list.
  
  Then then a call to ./doitall does the build, pack and install of the 
  binaries in /usr/local/bin.
  Note that you have to have the sudo in your host and be in the sudoers to
  be able to write in the /usr/local/bin where cloonix is installed.

  Be aware that cloonix_config must be saved because it is overwritten
  with each new install.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Install from already compiled binaries found at cloonix.fr:
-----------------------------------------------------------

  To run the pre-compiled software, the host needs a subset of the packets
  needed for the build, see "REQUIRED PACKETS FOR RUN" for the list.

  To install the cloonix in a jessie for example, do as root:

         cd /usr/local/bin
         tar zxvf ${HOME}/jessie-cloonix-${VERSION}.tar.gz
         chown -R root:root /usr/local/bin/cloonix*

  If you need to create a tap with the cloonix server, you must add:

         MUTAP=/usr/local/bin/cloonix/server/muswitch/mutap/cloonix_mutap
         chmod u+s ${MUTAP}
  

To use the software, a virtual machine qcow2 is necessary:
----------------------------------------------------------

  After the install, download one of the virtual machines provided at
  cloonix.fr, choose the jessie.qcow2, and put it in your "bulk" directory,
  see in /usr/local/bin/cloonix/cloonix_config the path for the bulk
  directory which is by default ${HOME}/cloonix_data/bulk. 
  
Use a demo script to begin using cloonix:
-----------------------------------------

  Download one of the demo scripts provided at cloonix.fr, choose the 
  "ping.sh" script because it is the simplest one and launch it.
  


----------------------------
REQUIRED PACKETS FOR BUILD:
----------------------------

stretch jessie xenial
=====================

    apt-get install \
            tmux genisoimage rxvt-unicode bc build-essential \
            gcc-multilib libncurses5-dev libpulse-dev libssl-dev \
            libgtk-3-dev libcap-dev libevent-dev libreadline-dev \
            libsdl1.2-dev libogg-dev libsasl2-dev intltool \
            libjpeg-dev python-pyparsing libsoup2.4 libusb-1.0-0-dev \
            libgudev-1.0-dev libopus-dev python-six \
            libtext-csv-perl libepoxy-dev libegl1-mesa-dev


centos-7
========

    yum -y install \
           tmux genisoimage tar xterm make gcc gcc-c++ m4 bc \
           glibc-devel.i686 glibc-devel.x86_64 libstdc++-devel.i686 \
           flex bison  bzip2 patch diffutils gtk3-devel \
           dejavu-serif-fonts SDL-devel libcap-devel ncurses-devel \
           readline-devel libevent-devel e2fsprogs alsa-lib-devel \
           opus-devel pulseaudio-libs-devel libsoup-devel pyparsing \
           libusb-devel libgudev1-devel libgusb-devel intltool \
           openssl-devel pulseaudio-libs-devel pixman-devel \
           gobject-introspection-devel libjpeg-turbo-devel \
           zlib-devel cyrus-sasl-devel gtk-doc python-six \
           cpan libepoxy-devel"

      export PERL_MM_USE_DEFAULT=1; cpan install Text::CSV




fedora-24
=========

    dnf -y install \
           tmux genisoimage tar rxvt-unicode make gcc gcc-c++ m4 bc \
           glibc-devel.i686 glibc-devel.x86_64 libstdc++-devel.i686 \
           flex bison  bzip2 patch diffutils gtk3-devel \
           dejavu-serif-fonts SDL-devel libcap-devel ncurses-devel \
           readline-devel libevent-devel e2fsprogs alsa-lib-devel \
           opus-devel pulseaudio-libs-devel libsoup-devel pyparsing \
           libusb-devel libgudev1-devel libgusb-devel intltool \
           openssl-devel pulseaudio-libs-devel pixman-devel \
           gobject-introspection-devel libjpeg-turbo-devel \
           zlib-devel cyrus-sasl-devel gtk-doc python-six \
           perl-Text-CSV libepoxy-devel


opensuse-42-2
=============

    zypper install \
           tmux genisoimage tar rxvt-unicode make \
           gcc gcc-c++ m4 bc gcc-32bit flex \
           bison e2fsprogs bzip2 patch diffutils libopenssl-devel \
           gtk3-devel dejavu-fonts libcap-devel \
           ncurses-devel readline-devel libevent-devel libSDL-devel \
           python-gtk-devel python-pyparsing libjpeg62-devel \
           libogg-devel cyrus-sasl-devel alsa-devel libpulse-devel \
           intltool libsoup-devel libXrandr-devel libusb-devel \
           libgudev-1_0-devel libopus-devel python-six \
           perl-Text-CSV libepoxy-devel


